      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The striking millworkers declared\nboycott on the King Sash & Door\ncompany, Harcleroad & Westphal\nCo., Post Falls and Inland mills yes\nterday afternoon.\n\n\nThe millmen have retaliated by\nsaying they can get sash and door\nframes from the Tacoma mills in\nsufficient quantities to fill immediate\norders.\n\n\nFrom the standpoint Of the small\nmillowners the strike situation IL\nmore discouraging than at any time\nsince the trouble started. 1t had been\nhoped that the boycott would not be\nresorted to-that the differences\nwould adjust themselves without the\nAeceseity of extraordinary measures\nThe strikers. on the other hand, felt\nthat they were forced to adopt sx-\ntraordinary measures because Of the\ntactics Of the millowners to keep\ntheir affairs running despite the\nstrike."
    }
